I created my infographic using Canva, a user-friendly design tool that provides templates, icons, and layout options. The design presents a “Digital  Literacy Student Guide” that combines key aspects of digital awareness in a single visual. It includes sections on digital literacy, useful digital tools for students, safe internet practices, and email etiquette. Each section is organized using a clear grid layout with defined colours and icons to improve readability and visual appeal. The goal of the design is to help students quickly understand how to use technology effectively, stay safe online, and communicate professionally.
One interesting aspect I found while creating the infographic was how important visual hierarchy is. Choosing the right colours, font sizes, and icons made a big difference in making the content easy to understand at a glance. 
I found it slightly difficult to balance the amount of information—ensuring the content was informative but not overcrowded. 
This process helped me improve both my design thinking and my ability to present information concisely.
